headline: Does T-Mobile Still Offer Value After Recent 5G Expansion and Share Price Softness?
summary: Wondering whether T-Mobile US at around $204 a share is a bargain or a trap? This breakdown will walk you through what the current price is really implying about the business. The stock is down 2.7% over the last week, 1.2% over the past month, and 6.9% year to date, but longer term it is still up 50.5% over three years and 62.8% over five, which hints that the recent weakness may just be a pause in a much bigger story. headline: Tyk Marks 10 Years in Business by Proving British Tech Can Grow Responsibly
summary: ATLANTA, December 09, 2025--Tyk, the independent UK software company powering millions of digital transactions worldwide, is marking its tenth anniversary with B Corp certification - a milestone that recognises a decade of growth built on purpose, not hype.

headline: AT&T Joins T-Mobile In Digital Switching As Wireless Industry Faces Big Changes
summary: AT&T will join T-Mobile in adopting digital switching for customers. The move is likely to increase industry customer turnover rates. AT&T stock dipped.
